SHERIDAN FLOURING MILLS, Inc., v. Thomas K. CASSIDY, Collector of Internal Revenue for the District of Wyoming. No. 1556. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Nov. 24, 1937. George T. Evans, of Denver, Colo., for appellant. Carl L. Sackett, U. S. Atty., of Cheyenne, Wyo., for appellee.

Before LEWIS, PHILLIPS, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on application of appellant at appellant’s costs.
